latestPosts.caption:
What happens when you combine the soulful nostalgia of the 80s with the electrifying energy of progressive house? You get THIS. 

My latest track Fiona is a tribute to the golden era of music, created entirely with authentic 80s instruments. Think punchy drum machines, dreamy synth pads that bring back the vibe. 

It’s classy, it’s emotional, it’s high-energy, and it’s guaranteed to take you on a journey of pure bliss. 
Thank you @danmckiedj @1980recordings for this. 

💽 Now Streaming Everywhere

Electric Eden Records presents Tulum, the latest single from Indian artist Samir Khan. This track captures the essence of melodic house with warm, flowing rhythms and an immersive atmosphere that transports listeners to distant landscapes. Rich harmonies blend with organic textures, creating a deep and emotive soundscape that unfolds with precision and elegance. The composition builds with a steady groove, layering subtle percussions and evolving melodies that drive the energy forward. A balance of delicate synth work and hypnotic progression gives Tulum a timeless quality, drawing inspiration from the natural world while maintaining a refined, club-ready structure. Its fluid arrangement and dynamic elements make it a captivating addition to any set, resonating beyond the dancefloor. With Tulum, Electric Eden Records continues its vision of delivering forward-thinking electronic music. The single is now available on all major platforms. More about the label and its latest projects can be found at linktr.ee/electricedenrecords.
